{"id": "EUVD-2022-55886", "enisaUuid": "c6b28617-4092-33e0-8663-41e1f67a5456", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nsecurity: Restrict CONFIG_ZERO_CALL_USED_REGS to gcc or clang > 15.0.6\n\nA bad bug in clang's implementation of -fzero-call-used-regs can result\nin NULL pointer dereferences (see the links above the check for more\ninformation). Restrict CONFIG_CC_HAS_ZERO_CALL_USED_REGS to either a\nsupported GCC version or a clang newer than 15.0.6, which will catch\nboth a theoretical 15.0.7 and the upcoming 16.0.0, which will both have\nthe bug fixed.", "datePublished": "2025-12-30T12:08:29", "dateUpdated": "2026-01-02T15:04:47", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8a4236456a3a402f6bb92aa7b75e7a3b4ef7a72c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0b202dfedb5aa2e7d07d849be33fa3a48c026926", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/21ca0bfa11bbb9a9207f5d2104f47d3d71b4616e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d6a9fb87e9d18f3394a9845546bbe868efdccfd2", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50812"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50812"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0806436b-c837-3842-9a52-a5211a6038bd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.15"}, {"id": "4299b080-595f-314e-9e8b-9b3759bf19db", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a82adfd5c7cb4b8bb37ef439aed954f9972bb618 <0b202dfedb5aa2e7d07d849be33fa3a48c026926"}, {"id": "4c30941d-22b9-3912-961c-3dca8e3d7399", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "4e47b0a9-884f-3045-b26a-673b6f894b42", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <21ca0bfa11bbb9a9207f5d2104f47d3d71b4616e"}, {"id": "54ac4cec-8658-3c3d-8161-dee4c9dea648", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.86"}, {"id": "557c2045-2e17-3a73-82ac-79d06e47c943", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a82adfd5c7cb4b8bb37ef439aed954f9972bb618 <8